## Change 4: Fix account toggle persistence bug in `InvestmentBalanceChart`

**Goal:** When `accountBalances` prop changes (e.g. year filter changes), the `visible` state resets because it is initialized from `accounts` which is derived from `accountBalances`. This causes user toggle preferences to be lost on every year-range adjustment. Fix this so toggles persist across re-renders as long as the account (by key) still exists.

**File:** `client/src/components/Charts/InvestmentBalanceChart.tsx`

### Step 4a — Replace the `visible` state initialization and add a sync effect

Replace the current `useState` initializer:

```typescript
// REMOVE THIS:
const [visible, setVisible] = useState<Record<string, boolean>>(() =>
  Object.fromEntries(accounts.map(({ key }) => [key, true]))
);
```

With a ref-backed approach that preserves existing selections and only adds defaults for new accounts:

```typescript
const [visible, setVisible] = useState<Record<string, boolean>>({});

// Sync: when accounts list changes, add any NEW accounts as visible=true
// but do NOT reset accounts the user has already toggled
useEffect(() => {
  setVisible((prev) => {
    const updated = { ...prev };
    let changed = false;
    for (const { key } of accounts) {
      if (!(key in updated)) {
        updated[key] = true;
        changed = true;
      }
    }
    return changed ? updated : prev;
  });
}, [accounts]);
```

> This means: when a new account appears (new model added), it defaults to visible. When the year filter changes but accounts remain the same, user toggles are preserved.

